Q4: What happens if I leave before receiving my grants?\nA: In the event that you depart before receiving your RSU grants, they will vest according to the terms outlined in your original employment agreement. Typically, a pro-rata share of unvested RSUs may still accrue interest until the time of termination. For more details regarding specific circumstances, consult with Human Resources.\n',
'instruction': 'Summarize this article focusing on key points related to how the new hire RSU awards are determined and their visibility timeline without including any financial calculations or specific dates.'}
 New Hire Restricted Stock Units (RSUs) are awarded to employees upon joining a company. Conversion of the grant target value into U.S. dollars occurs using the 9-month average exchange rate on the first business day of the Hooli fiscal quarter corresponding to the employee's start date. This value is then divided by the average stock price over 21 consecutive trading days up to the end of the month containing the start date. The resulting figure determines the number of RSUs granted, which is displayed in the employee's Schwab account once vested but can only be viewed during the second week after the grant date. Unvested shares due to early departure vest according to the initial employment contract terms.

